ReadMe

Drill ID: JD_2026_06_W2_DisasterResponseSystem

Class Name: DisasterResponseMain

Difficulty: Level 2 — Multi-Class Application

Estimated Time: 50 minutes

Actual Time Taken: 43 minutes

Written by: Chanwoo Park

Problem
Build a disaster response simulation system using an abstract parent class
and several child classes that override an abstract method.

Requirements
- Create an abstract EmergencyUnit parent class.
- Create FireUnit, MedicalUnit, and RescueUnit child classes.
- Store emergency units in an EmergencyUnit array.
- Use a loop to print information and call overridden respond() methods.
- Count how many units are ready based on readiness.

Learning Objective
Practice abstraction by defining common structure in an abstract class,
then completing different behaviors in child classes through method overriding.
